\section*{Innate immunity.}
- adaptive response typically takes 1-2 weeks to develop
- in the meantime, innate immunity:
- contains the infection transiently
- induces adaptive T and B cell responses
- in many cases innate immunity is also involved in pathogen clearance during the peak of the adaptive response

\section*{Basic principles of immunity}
- defense is mediated by effector mechanisms aimed at containment and clearance
- pathogens receive specialized responses
- pathogen survival hinges around evasion of effector responses.

