\section*{Intracellular bacteria}
- adapted to replicate inside cells, often phagocytes
- no antibody accessibility => CMI is critical
- activation of NK cells => kill infected cells, secrete Th1 cytokines
- IL-12 => key to inducing a Th1 response
- macrophage activation via CD40L and IFN- $\gamma=>$ increases killing of ingested microbes
- induction of ROS, NO, lysosomal enzymes (anti-microbial)
- if bacteria escapes phagosomes -> cytosol, they can be recognized by CD8+ T cells

