\section*{Viral evasion}
- evolution (antigen variation)
- HLA down-regulation
- homologs to human proteins (EBV -> IL-10)
- CTL exhaustion

\section*{Parasites}
- infect $30 \%$ of the world's population
- protozoa, helminths, ectoparasites
- complex life cycles with intermediate hosts
- most cause chronic infections => weak innate immunity and evade adaptive responses

\section*{Parasites (2)}
- Innate:
- many parasites can resist phagocytosis
- some bind TLRs and activate APCs
- Adaptive:
- differs widely depending on life cycle, structure of the pathogen
- if intracellular => similar to intracellular bacteria
- extracellular => special types of antibody responses (lgE)

